Both the West Indies batters are now back in the shed and India are off to a perfect start in this Test match.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shardul Thakur gets a breakthrough in his very first over and India are all over the hosts in this first session of the Test match! This is bowled full and outside the off stump. Raymon Reifer is drawn into the shot this time and he looks for an expansive drive through the cover region. Gets a faint nick through to the keeper and Ishan Kishan does a great job diving forward to his left. He grabs hold of the ball and gets up celebrating. The umpires go upstairs to check for a fair catch and once the replays show it, Raymon Reifer begins to walk back to the dressing room. India have three wickets now and are well on top.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! That is a spectacular catch by Mohammed Siraj! He helps India get their fourth wicket at the stroke of Lunch! Ravindra Jadeja has his first wicket of the game as he tosses this one full and outside the off pole. Jermaine Blackwood decides to play a rash shot just before the break and pays the price. He looks to go over the mid off fielder but does not get the cleanest connection. The ball is looping to the right of Mohammed Siraj and seems to be going over him but he sticks his right hand out. He grabs hold of the ball and falls onto the ground but manages to keep his fingers clasped around the cherry. An absolute screamer by the pace bowler and India are right on top in this tie. With the fall of the wicket, the umpires have decided to call it LUNCH on DAY 1.
Default_Commentary: 27.6: Ravindra Jadeja to Jermaine Blackwood, OUT! c Mohammed Siraj b Ravindra Jadeja.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: WICKET! The local lad Alick Athanaze gets the first breakthrough! Flatter and spins back into the batter on the middle and leg. Rohit Sharma lunges forward to defend but it takes the glove on the way and hits the pad. The ball lobs up toward short leg and Joshua Da Silva runs in to take a sharp catch. A huge appeal from West Indies but umpire is unmoved! They take the review and the replays show and inside edge on the glove giving West Indies their first wicket.  A fine knock from the Indian skipper comes to an end as he walks back for a well-made 103.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Alzarri Joseph gets the breakthrough and Yashasvi Jaiswal's remarkable inning comes to an end! What a wonderful inning it has been by the youngster and the disappointment on his face shows that he is still not happy about getting out! This is bowled slightly back of a length and outside the off stump. Yashasvi Jaiswal throws his bat at this one and gets a faint edge through to the keeper. Joshua Da Silva grabs hold of the ball and goes up in celebration as the umpire raises his finger. Jaiswal walks back to the shed amidst loud applause from the crowd and his dressing room as India lose their third wicket. What a talent they have in their hands.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! An absolute beauty from Ravichandran Ashwin and it did not take him long to get into the act! His ploy to come 'round the wicket in this over has worked immediately and he squares up the West Indies captain. This is bowled slightly short and pitching on middle. The ball keeps his line and Kraigg Brathwaite is stuck in the crease unable to decide whether to go forward or stay back. Ends up poking his bat at the ball and gets an outside edge towards slip. Ajinkya Rahane takes a sharp catch and India have their second wicket. Both their spinners have one wicket each and have their tails up. West Indies are in a spot of bother with both their openers back in the shed.

Ashwin floats this one up, full and on off, grips and turns in sharply, Jermaine Blackwood prods forward to block, but plays down the wrong line to get hit on the pads right in front of the stumps.
